    "body": "The double click is already in my svg branch.  Resizing looks better with svg's\nanyway.  ;)\n\nI was also thinking of double click maximizing the width, when it's at its\ndefault size, and restricting the size so you can't make it wider than the\nbrowser's width...\n\nMin RK [reply@reply.github.com] wrote:\n\n> I think double-click to reset zoom solves the problem in the simplest way, rather than giving all images a mode.  It has no conflict with any possible existing events, because we should never bind events to the whole output area, which would necessarily conflict with interactive widgets.\n> \n> ---\n> \n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub:\n> \n> ## https://github.com/ipython/ipython/pull/1887#issuecomment-6339382\n> \n> Cheers, Bob McElrath\n\n\"The individual has always had to struggle to keep from being overwhelmed by\nthe tribe.  If you try it, you will be lonely often, and sometimes frightened.\nBut no price is too high to pay for the privilege of owning yourself.\" \n    -- Friedrich Nietzsche\n"
